# Error Files

Apply these conventions to every `app/api/errors/*-error.js` file.

## Structure

- Use `"use strict";` at the top of the file.
- Import and use the project base error class from `app/api/errors/`.
- Name files in kebab-case with `-error.js` suffix.
- Group related errors into exported objects (for example by use case or external service).
- Export only groups that are actually defined in the file.

## Error Classes

- Every custom error class extends the project base error class.
- Keep error codes deterministic and namespaced by group/use case.
- Keep error messages concise, human-readable, and action-oriented.
- Keep constructor signature and `super(...)` call style consistent with the project base error implementation.
